description: Manual test case generation in structured JSON format
requirement: User should be able to log in using email and password.
prompt_used:
You are a senior QA engineer. Generate detailed manual test cases for the following requirement:

User should be able to log in using email and password.

Return the output **only in valid JSON** format (no explanations, no markdown). The JSON must be an array of objects, where each object has the following structure:

[
  {
    "test_case": "Unique ID or Title of the test case",
    "objective": "Purpose of this test case",
    "preconditions": ["Any preconditions required"],
    "test_data": ["List of test data items"],
    "test_steps": ["Step 1", "Step 2", "..."],
    "expected_results": ["Expected result 1", "Expected result 2"],
    "variations": ["Optional variations if any"],
    "edge_cases": ["Edge cases or negative tests"]
  }
]

⚠️ Important: Do not include any text outside of the JSON. Do not include markdown. Make sure it is valid JSON.

structured_test_cases.test_case: Login with Valid Email and Password
structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user can log in using a valid email and password
test_steps: Enter email address in email field
Verify user is logged in successfully
expected_results: User name is displayed at top right corner of the screen
User can see all his/her data

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user cannot log in using an invalid email
test_steps: Enter invalid email address in email field
Enter valid password in password field
expected_results: Error message indicating email is not registered is displayed

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user cannot log in using an invalid password
test_steps: Enter valid email address in email field
Enter incorrect password in password field
expected_results: Error message indicating password is incorrect is displayed

structured_test_cases.test_case: Login with Empty Email and Password
structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user cannot log in using an empty email and password
test_steps: Leave both email and password fields blank
expected_results: Error message indicating email and password are required is displayed
